I&#39;ll admit up front that this took me way longer to figure out than it should have (I&#39;m new to postgres). The key &quot;duh&quot; moment was realizing it was behaving just like a foreground process when you close a terminal window -- i.e., closing the window kills the foreground process. So then I realized when launchctl was done launching &quot;pg_ctl&quot; some process exited and pg_ctl was dying as a result.

