The easily way to do it is to delete the `&lt;Target&gt;` and `&lt;/Target&gt;`. See the example from [official document](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/visualstudio/msbuild/choose-element-msbuild?view=vs-2019#example):

    &lt;Project  xmlns=&quot;http://schemas.microsoft.com/developer/msbuild/2003&quot; &gt;
      &lt;PropertyGroup&gt;
        ...
      &lt;/PropertyGroup&gt;
      &lt;Choose&gt;
        &lt;When Condition=&quot; &#39;$(Configuration)&#39;==&#39;debug&#39; &quot;&gt;
          &lt;ItemGroup&gt;
            ...
          &lt;/ItemGroup&gt;
        &lt;/When&gt;
        &lt;When Condition=&quot; &#39;$(Configuration)&#39;==&#39;retail&#39; &quot;&gt;
          &lt;PropertyGroup&gt;
            ...
          &lt;/PropertyGroup&gt;
        &lt;/When&gt;
        &lt;Otherwise&gt;
            ...
        &lt;/Otherwise&gt;
      &lt;/Choose&gt;
      &lt;Target Name=&quot;Test&quot;&gt;
        ...
      &lt;/Target&gt;
    &lt;/Project&gt;

So the correct level should be:

    ----Project
    ------Choose
    --------When
    ------Target

The `choose` tag should be the same level like `target`. So you get the first error `The element &lt;When&gt; beneath element &lt;Choose&gt; is unrecognized`. And I assume the reason why the issue still occurs after you put the `choose` tag outside `Target` is that you didn&#39;t copy the Choose tag and its content(when...) outside together. Then you may get error like `The element &lt;Target&gt; beneath element &lt;Choose&gt; is unrecognized`. 

The easy way to resolve this is to delete the `&lt;Target&gt; and &lt;/Target&gt;`, then you can reload the project file. If I misunderstand anything, feel free to let me know :)

